ce:section.ce:para:
In order to study the practical application potential of the method, water samples were spiked with different MnO4
                        − and N2H4 concentrations and analyzed. Tap water is obtained from the laboratory and river water was taken from the Chang jiang in Nanjing (China) and centrifuged at 10000 rpm for 20 min. They were then filtered through 0.22 µm microporous membrane. MnO4
                        − recovery was between 97.34% and 104.0%. RSDs ranged from 0.67% to 5.1% (Tables 1
                        ). The recovery of N2H4 in sample was between 97.56% and 104.4%. RSDs ranged from 0.51% to 2.2% (Tables 2
                        ). These results confirm the reliability and the feasibility of such N-CDs fluorescent probe for monitoring MnO4
                        − and N2H4 in real environmental water samples.
